msg.content: Who are the 5 longest-reigning monarchs and who were their fathers?
Who are the 5 longest-reigning monarchs and who were their fathers?

Sure! Here are the five longest-reigning monarchs and their fathers:

1. King Louis XIV of France (72 years, 110 days - longest reigning monarch in European history): Son of Louis XIII of France

2. Bhumibol Adulyadej (70 years, 126 days - longest-reigning monarch in Thai history): Son of Mahidol Adulyadej, Prince of Songkla, the Prince Father of Thailand

3. Johann II of Liechtenstein (70 years, 91 days): Son of Prince Franz I of Liechtenstein

4. K'inich Janaab' Pakal or 'Pakal the Great' (68 years - longest-reigning ruler of the Classic Maya civilization of Mexico's history): Son of K'an Mo' Hix

5. Bing of Han (61 years, 240 days - longest-reigning monarch in Chinese history): Son of Liu Xun
